      <txt c="X" a="X" r="X" s="2" w="850" x="40" y="80" delay="0" pt="1" e="-3" align="left">A ship is at berth and the agent calls the company and offers to pay some money to the health authorities so that they forget about miscalculation of the medicine on board the ship.

Can the company be liable if the agent gives some money to the health authorities?</txt>
      <txt c="X" s="2" y="200" delay="0" crct="35" align="left">Yes, it is a bribe</txt>
      <txt c="X" s="2" y="260" delay="0" crct="85" align="left">Yes, it is a facilitation payment</txt>
